<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910503-0124</DOCNO><DOCID>910503-0124.</DOCID><HL>   NCNB Agrees to Sell   10 Million New Shares</HL><DATE>05/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8</SO><CO>   NCB STB</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>ALL REGIONAL BANKS (BAR)SOUTHERN U.S. BANKS (BAS)ALL BANKS, BANKING NEWS AND ISSUES (BNK)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>STOCK andamp; OTHER MARKET NEWS (STK)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>FLORIDA (FL)NORTH CAROLINA (NC)</RE><LP>   CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- NCNB Corp. said it entered a purchaseagreement to sell 10 million newly issued shares of itscommon stock for $37.25 a share.   The bank holding company said that of the total, 8.5million shares will be sold to investors in the U.S. and 1.5million to investors in Europe. The closing date for the saleof the shares is expected to be May 9, the company said.</LP><TEXT>   An NCNB spokesman acknowledged that proceeds of its stocksale could be used to buy Miami-based Southeast BankingCorp., but in a statement NCNB cited a host of other possibleuses as well. NCNB said the $362 million will be used for&quot;general corporate purposes, possible additionalcontributions to the capital of its subsidaries, or possibleacquisitions of other financial institutions or their assets,including failed institutions.&quot;   NCNB said last week that it is considering making a bidfor loss-ridden Southeast. An NCNB spokesman declined tocomment on the status of talks with Southeast. Barnett BanksInc., Jacksonville, Fla., confirmed this week that it, too,is considering bidding for Southeast. Southeast officialsdeclined to comment.   Merrill Lynch andamp; Co. is leading a syndicate ofunderwriters.   In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchangeyesterday, NCNB's stock closed at $37.25 a share, up 12.5cents.</TEXT></DOC>